<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>6 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS INTERNATIONAL MODEL ES52-7A AND ESO65-7A 6-PLUS - DISASSEMBLY - MAIN CASE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="19">
        <title>MAIN CASE</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Continue by removing the two intermediate bear ing plates. The mainshaft bearing plate has
                an oil trough which will be removed with the plate. The large oil trough connected to the housing
                doesn't have to be removed,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300629">Figure 29</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300629" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300629" filename="../figg13/G1300629.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 29. Remove Intermediate Bearing Plates</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lock the transmission into two gears, then remove the mainshaft intermediate nut,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300630">Figure 30</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300630" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300630" filename="../figg13/G1300630.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 30. Remove Mainshaft Intermediate Nut</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove mainshaft and countershaft bearing snap rings,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300631">Figure 31</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300631" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300631" filename="../figg13/G1300631.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 31. Mainshaft and Countershaft Bearing Snap Rings</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use pry bars to remove the mainshaft and countershaft bearings,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300632">Figure 32</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300632" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300632" filename="../figg13/G1300632.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 32. Mainshaft and Countershaft Bearings</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a chain hoist to remove main case housing,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300633">Figure 33</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300633" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300633" filename="../figg13/G1300633.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 33. Remove Main Case Housing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lift the mainshaft from the case with the help of a hoist. It may be necessary to tilt the
                counter shaft to the side for clearance. Note that the 1st/2nd and 3rd/4th speed forks lift out of the
                housing with the mainshaft,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300634">Figure 34</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300634" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300634" filename="../figg13/G1300634.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 34. Mainshaft From Case</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1300635">Figure 35</hotlnk>
            for exploded view of main gear.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1300635" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1300635" filename="../figg13/G1300635.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 35. Exploded View of Main Gear</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the forks from the mainshaft,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300636">Figure 36</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300636" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300636" filename="../figg13/G1300636.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 36. Remove Forks From Mainshaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tilt the countershaft and lift it from the housing,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300637">Figure 37</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300637" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300637" filename="../figg13/G1300637.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 37. Lift Countershaft From Housing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide the synchronizer away from the fork clips,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300638">Figure 38</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300638" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300638" filename="../figg13/G1300638.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 38. Synchronizer Away From Fork Clips</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The overdrive fork is pictured here (Code 13MAH transmission),
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300639">Figure 39</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300639" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300639" filename="../figg13/G1300639.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 39. Overdrive Fork</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The direct shift fork, shown at left, is removed at this time,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300640">Figure 40</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300640" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300640" filename="../figg13/G1300640.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 40. Direct Shift Fork</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If the overdrive shift bar is worn, remove the snap ring and pin (arrow). Replace the bar,
                and secure it with the shift fork mounting pin and snap ring,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300641">Figure 41</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300641" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300641" filename="../figg13/G1300641.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 41. Overdrive Shift Bar</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If the fork clips on either the direct or overdrive shift fork are worn, they are pulled off
                and re placed,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300642">Figure 42</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300642" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300642" filename="../figg13/G1300642.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 42. Replace Fork Clips</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Next, tip the clutch housing up. Remove the four drive gear bearing cap capscrews,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300643">Figure 43</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300643" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300643" filename="../figg13/G1300643.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 43. Remove Drive Gear Bearing Cap Capscrews</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1300644">Figure 44</hotlnk>, exploded view of clutch housing and shift forks.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1300644" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1300644" filename="../figg13/G1300644.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 44. Exploded View of Clutch Housing and Shift Forks</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position a pry bar in the milled slot of the clutch housing and pry the bearing retainer
                away from the housing,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300645">Figure 45</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300645" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300645" filename="../figg13/G1300645.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 45. Pry Bearing Retainer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove bearing retainer and oil baffle. Then tap the drive gear out of the clutch housing,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300646">Figure 46</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300646" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300646" filename="../figg13/G1300646.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 46. Drive Gear Out of Clutch Housing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove snap ring and oil ring from main drive gear. Then press main drive gear bearing from
                gear,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300647">Figure 47</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300647" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300647" filename="../figg13/G1300647.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 47. Drive Gear Bearing From Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
